The paper discusses the generation of interfaces for personalized interaction with digital libraries, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), digital libraries (cs.DL), and potentially cybernetics (cs.CY) in terms of the interaction between the user and the system.
